cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with a computer vision problem of establishing dense visual correspondence across different object instances. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves 3D CAD models and rendering, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GR (Graphics) as well. The use of deep learning techniques for training a ConvNet makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of supervisory signals, which could suggest it belongs to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with image matching, which could also suggest it belongs to cs.MM (Multimedia).
